- 'moved' refers to items that have been transferred from one location to another;
- 'more requested than requisitioned' means the total quantity requested is greater than the number of requisition entries;
- 'more moved than recorded' means the total quantity moved is greater than the number of movement entries;
- 'available in New York' means the items are stored in a location within the city of New York;
- 'companies based in New York' means the companies are located in the city and state of New York.

- "Guardians" refers to the users who have moved items the most;
- "Treasures" refers to the items in the database;
- "Most frequently moved" indicates the highest number of movements for each item.

- 'Non-requestable' means the item cannot be requested by other departments;
- 'Categorized as 0' refers to a specific category of items, which may be defined by the system or organization;
